rical lexicography of German, Dutch, and English with a focus on factors related to ideological history, professional lexicography, and cultural education. In the main part of the book, the author undertakes a professional treatment of the common types of lexicographic information, and also gives a discussion of some rarely provided lexicographic information.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aDutch languagexLexicography. 0aEnglish languagexLexicography. 0aGerman languagexLexicography. 0aGermanic languagesxLexicography. 0aLexicography. 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aGeistes- und Kulturgeschichte. 4aLexikographie. 4aMittelalter/Geistes- und Kulturleben. 4aSemantik/Lexikon. 4aWörterbuch. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / German.2bisacsh  aLexicography.  aMiddle Ages/intellectual and cultural life.  aearly modern era.  aintellectual and cultural history.  asemantics/lexicon.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2012z9783110288896oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311028255940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311028269640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110282696423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110282696/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2012  aZDB-23-DGGb2012  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014